title: Israel Considers Filing Charges Against Soldiers Over Death of Palestinian-American
description: The Israeli military said it is considering filing charges against two soldiers over the death of Omar Assad, a 78-year-old Palestinian-American who died after he was detained by Israeli soldiers at an impromptu West Bank checkpoint.

title: U.K. Sanctions Have Frozen More Than $21 Billion in Russian Assets
description: The U.K. said it plans to ramp up sanctions to ‘exert maximum economic pressure’

title: South Korea to Sell Arms to U.S. for Ukraine
description: Artillery units are to be supplied for at least several weeks of intensive combat.

title: Kremlin's Backers Rush to Defend Russia's Retreat From Kherson
description: Hard-line nationalists, however, are growing frustrated with Moscow’s repeated setbacks in Ukraine.

title: Venezuela Opposition Leader Juan Guaidó Vows to Fight On
description: In an interview with The Wall Street Journal, the so-called interim president discusses his struggle against the growing power of the Maduro regime.

title: Iran Fails to Provide Answers to U.N. in Nuclear-Material Probe
description: Iran hasn’t offered any new answers to the United Nations atomic agency’s probe into nuclear material found in Tehran, the International Atomic Energy Agency said, opening the way for a fresh formal rebuke of Iran from member states, diplomats said.

title: Gabon Targets a Huge Payday With Carbon Credits
description: The deeply forested African country is trying to issue and sell large volumes of carbon credits to take advantage of potential revenue from its emission reductions, but the planned sale is roiling the carbon markets.

title: Thousands Protest Against Inflation in France
description: The new demonstrations are a sign of the political turmoil facing European leaders as the region teeters on the brink of recession.

title: U.S. Warns Israel It Will Fight Attempts to Annex West Bank
description: The Biden administration warned Israel against trying to annex parts of the West Bank, underscoring how Benjamin Netanyahu’s far-right coalition partners could complicate U.S.-Israeli relations if they try to fulfill their most controversial campaign promises.

title: Ukraine Is Wary of Russia's Kherson Retreat, Fearing a Trap
description: Ukrainian officials urged caution about Russia’s announced withdrawal from the southern city, as U.S. officials estimated that 100,000 troops on each side had been killed or wounded since the war began.

title: Ukraine's Battlefield Gains Likely to Slow After Swift Victories
description: Kyiv’s forces face mounting obstacles in achieving battlefield gains as they confront Russian troops that are dug in more deeply and the weather slows the tempo of fighting.

title: Russian Oligarch Abramovich Wins Apology From Police in Channel Islands
description: A local court ordered Jersey police to apologize and pay damages to the billionaire after it concluded warrants to search properties linked to him were gained unlawfully.

title: China's Billionaires See Huge Losses as Economy, Markets Sputter
description: The zero-Covid policy, plunging share values and a property slump have erased hundreds of billions of dollars from coffers of the country’s tycoons.

title: Biden Plans to Meet China's Xi and Discuss How to Avoid Conflict
description: President Biden said he plans to discuss how the U.S. and China can avoid conflict when he meets with Chinese leader Xi Jinping during his coming Asia trip, but won’t make concessions on critical issues.
